{{other uses|E-Pro (disambiguation)}}
{{lowercase}}
'''e-Pro''' (styled '''e-PRO''') is an [[Internet]] [[professional certification]] program approved by the [[National Association of Realtors]] (NAR) for its members.<ref>[http://www.realtor.org/runivers.nsf/pages/designation?OpenDocument  NAR's list of its designations offered]</ref>  Members of the [[Canadian Real Estate Association]] (CREA) may also pursue the e-Pro certification and use the [[trademark|logo]] by completing the [[electronic learning|online learning]] program.

The four core areas of study (arranged in modules) are:
# Internet fundamentals (e.g., [[Internet service provider]]s, [[electronic mailing list]]s, [[domain name]]s, and [[domain name system|DNS]]).
# [[E-mail]] communication methods and strategies for clients/customers.
# The [[World Wide Web]] and its uses in developing a real estate business.
# Other technology ([[Computer hardware|hardware]] and [[computer software|software]], both general purpose and [[real estate]] industry-specific).

The course material prior to 2010 was based on the ''Real Estate Technology Guide''.<ref>Barnett, Mike; Klein, Saul; and [[John Reilly (lawyer)|Reilly, John]], ''Real Estate Technology Guide'', Dearborn Real Estate Education, 2003 {{ISBN|978-0-7931-7732-5}}</ref>

In 2010 the entire e-Pro course was re-written by Bill Lublin and his team at the Social Media Marketing Institute. The new course was the winner of the 2011 Award for best educational offering from the Real Estate Educators Association (REEA).

