{{Infobox School | name = Framhaldsskólinn í Austur-Skaftafellssýslu | image = | imagesize = | caption = | streetaddress = Nýheimar, Litlabrú 2 | city = {{flagicon|ISL}} [[Höfn]] | country = [[Iceland]] | coordinates = {{coord|64|15|11|N|15|12|45|W|region:IS_type:edu|display=inline}} | principal = Eyjólfur Guðmundsson | viceprincipal = | staff = 23 | gender = | type = | language = [[Icelandic language|Icelandic]] | classrooms = 8 | motto = | motto_translation = | nickname = FAS | opened = August 1, 1987 | established = August 1, 1987 | status = Open | pupils = around 200 | homepage = [http://www.fas.is/ http://www.fas.is] }} '''Framhaldsskólinn í Austur-Skaftafellssýslu''' (often abbreviated '''FAS''') is a secondary school located in [[Höfn]], southeast [[Iceland]]. It was founded in 1987 by the Icelandic government and municipalities in [[Austur-Skaftafellssýsla]]. The first 15 years, it was located in Nesjaskóli, in Nes, a nearby rural area, but was moved to a new building, Nýheimar, in 2002. The school has about 200 students, mostly locals, but distance education is also quite common.<ref>{{cite web|title=Um skólann - fas.is|url=http://www.fas.is/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=4&Itemid=18|publisher=Framhaldsskólinn í Austur-Skaftafellssýslu|accessdate=14 February 2014|language=Icelandic}}</ref> Current principal is Eyjólfur Guðmundsson.<ref>{{cite web|title=Starfsfólk - fas.is|url=http://www.fas.is/images/stories/frettir_h13/starf_fas_h13.pdf|publisher=Framhaldsskólinn í Austur-Skaftafellssýslu|accessdate=14 February 2014|language=Icelandic|format=pdf document, 116 kb.|quote=Look for the Icelandic word "Skólameistari"}}</ref>
