{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2018}} {{Use Indian English|date=August 2018}} '''Vaktrutvottejak Sabha''' is an organization best known for hosting the '''Vasant Vyakhyanmala''' (the traditional annual spring lecture series) every year since 1875 in [[Pune]], India. Justice [[Mahadeo Govind Ranade]] founded Vaktrutvottejak Sabha.<ref>{{cite news|title=Month-long spring lecture series that has been a tradition for centuries in Pune will be held till May 20.|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/pune/report-vasant-vyakhyanmala-a-century-old-lecture-series-kicks-off-in-pune-1980780|accessdate=9 December 2014|agency=dna|publisher=dna}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Vasant Vyakhyanmala to start from April 21|url=http://www.sakaaltimes.com/NewsDetails.aspx?NewsId=4714231410731082713&SectionId=5171561142064258099&SectionName=Pune&NewsDate=20110419&NewsTitle=Vasant%20Vyakhyanmala%20to%20start%20from%20April%2021|accessdate=9 December 2014|agency=sakaltimes|issue=19 April 2011|publisher=sakal news papers|date=19 April 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Month-long spring lecture series that has been a tradition for centuries in Pune will be held till May 20.|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/pune/report-vasant-vyakhyanmala-a-century-old-lecture-series-kicks-off-in-pune-1980780|accessdate=9 December 2014|agency=dna|publisher=dna}}</ref> Currently, Dr. [[Deepak Jayantrao Tilak]] is President of Vaktrutvottejak Sabha.
==Vasant Vyakhyanmala== {{Infobox organization | name = Vasant Vyakhyanmala | former name = | image = | alt = | caption = | motto = | predecessor = | successor = | formation = 1875 | type = Traditional annual spring lecture series | status = | location = [[Pune]], India | leader_title = | leader_name = Dr. Deepak Jayantrao Tilak (President), Dr. Mandar Bedekar (Chief Organizer) | budget = | num_staff = | num_volunteers = | website = }} The idea behind the series was to present a variety of lectures, across various topics to the people. In the later half of 19th century newspapers were primitive and live lectures were the most effective medium for knowledge transfer.<ref>{{cite web|title=‘Vasant Vyakhyanmala’ (Spring Lecture Series) – A Great 140 Year Tradition|url=https://aparanjape.wordpress.com/2014/04/20/vasant-vyakhyanmala-spring-lecture-series-a-great-140-year-tradition/|accessdate=10 December 2014}}</ref> Subjects from diverse fields like cultural, social,science, health, literature, finance, law, education, youth and history are covered in the lecture series usually organized at [[Tilak Smarak Ranga Mandir|Tilak Smarak Mandir]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Vasant Vyakhyanmala to start from April 21|url=http://www.sakaaltimes.com/NewsDetails.aspx?NewsId=4714231410731082713&SectionId=5171561142064258099&SectionName=Pune&NewsDate=20110419&NewsTitle=Vasant%20Vyakhyanmala%20to%20start%20from%20April%2021|accessdate=9 December 2014|agency=sakaltimes|issue=Tuesday, 19 April 2011|publisher=sakal news papers|date=19 April 2011}}</ref> For many years, the Vasant Vyankhyanmala was held at Hirabag and Belbag. It has been held at its present venue – Tilak Smarak Mandir, for many decades.<ref>{{cite web|title=‘Vasant Vyakhyanmala’ (Spring Lecture Series) – A Great 140 Year Tradition|url=https://aparanjape.wordpress.com/2014/04/20/vasant-vyakhyanmala-spring-lecture-series-a-great-140-year-tradition/|accessdate=10 December 2014}}</ref> The Vyakhanmala is held every year in the month of April or May i.e. Spring (''Vasant'' Rutu/Season).
=== Speakers === Eminent speakers are chosen from a diverse range of fields like doctors, entrepreneurs, writers, politicians and scholars who consider contemporary issues at the intersection of social issues, culture, science, health, literature, law, education, economy from a critical perspective.
